tel 1.0 https://tel-lang.org/schema/tel-schema

# A worked example of a TEL schema: a "contact" record type.
#
# Demonstrates the constructs an everyday schema author will reach for:
#
#   - required and optional `field`s of named scalar types (`String`)
#   - a `repeatable` field (`phone`)
#   - named `record`s (`PhoneNumber`, `Address`) referenced from
#     multiple positions
#   - a named top-level `select` (`Status`) with all-`Flag` variants,
#     placed as a `SelectRef` at the use site so it can also be set
#     inline as an atom on the parent compound
#   - a per-field `default` value (`country`)
#
# Every `field` and `variant` carries its type as an inline atom after
# any flags; type names are PascalCase and resolve to either a user-
# declared `record`/`scalar`/`select` or one of the predefined names
# `Flag`, `String`, `Identifier`, `Sigil`.
#
# To see what a document conforming to this schema looks like, see the
# accompanying `contact-document.tel`. This schema document is itself
# validated against the tel-schema (the schema-for-schemas) at parse time.

name contact

record PhoneNumber
  field country-code String
  field number String

record Address
  field street String
  field city String
  field country String unknown

select Status
  variant active Flag
  variant archived Flag

document
  field name String
  field email String optional
  field phone PhoneNumber optional repeatable
  field home Address optional
  field work Address optional
  select Status optional
